Privacy Policy
This privacy policy has been written in order show how RepCount uses your personal data. If you have any questions on how your data is used after reading this policy, feel free to contact us at info@repcountapp.com
By installing RepCount or using our services you agree for RepCount to process personal data on your behalf according to the policy listed in this document.
What personal data do we collect?
When you register a RepCount account we collect personal data from you such as your email address. When continuing to use the app you upload personal data, such as gym workouts and bodyweight data to your account.
As we want to improve our services, we may collect additional personal data in the future. If that happens, we will make sure to notify you about our privacy policy updates.
If you have enabled integrations with Apple Health or Google's Health Connect, RepCount can optionally collect data about your workouts from other apps and body measurements. This data can be used to analyze your workouts from within RepCount. Optionally RepCount can collect your gender to improve estimates for calories burned during your workout.
How we use your personal data
Your privacy is important! Thus we only use your privacy policy in accordance to with this privacy policy. Your personal data belongs to you and will not be shared with third parties (except for those that are processing data on RepCounts behalf), without your explicit permission to do so. Examples of explicit data sharing with third parties is if you enable RepCount to share workouts, body measurements and energy expenditure with Apple Health or Google's Health Connect.
Other information about app usage, crash logs etc may be shared with our partners in order for us to be able to improve your app experience.
Marketing
RepCount may use your email to send you updates and offers on the RepCount service. You may opt out from marketing at any time by unsubscribing.
Data processors
RepCount will never transfer data to third parties to use other than on the behalf of RepCount. Personal data may only be shared with third parties that process data on RepCounts behalf, such as data storage, authentication providers, crash reporting tools and customer messaging services. Third parties are not allowed to use your data in any other way than to provide services for RepCount unless you have given your explicit consent to do allow them to do so.
Security
We use industry standard mechanisms for authentication to prevent unauthorized access. Please make sure to use a strong password for your selected authentication method.
Data removal
If you decide you do not want to use RepCount anymore you may delete your account from within your app or by sending us an email at info@repcountapp.com. Deleting your account will remove your account info and the associated data.
Data Portability
You have the right to receive your personal data which you have provided to RepCount in accordance with relevant personal data regulation, provided that such request does not adversely affect the rights and freedoms of others. Data is made available upon request
Contact us
If you have any questions, feel free to contact us at info@repcountapp.com
Consent
By agreeing to these terms and conditions you are giving us permission to process your data for the purposes specified. Any other purposes would require your explicit consent.